				\begin{document}$${E}_{t}^{\text{'}}$$\end{document}Et' represent residuals. In our study, the time series for each amygdalar subregion (VLA, MedA or DorA) was defined as time series X, and the time series of each voxel in its interconnected social network (PerN, AffN or AveN) was defined as Y. GC between each amygdalar subregion and voxels of the respective brain network was studied using bivariate coefficient GCA. Finally, we converted GCA maps for all subjects to z-values using Fisher’s r-to-z transformation.

Specifically, we created an age-related GLM to examine GC changes between amygdalar subregions (VLA, MedA and DorA) and their corresponding brain networks (PerN, AffN and AveN) during life. In order to investigate the casual interaction between amygdalar subregions and social networks for ageing individuals, we established multiple linear regression equations with gender as covariate and age2 as the predictive factor. Concretely, the GLM model can be expressed with the following equations:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
